This is a collection of toys written in BASIC that can be played with.

Additional toys and examples of C-library bindings to BASIC programs and graphics interfaces etc can be found at:

http://www.basic-converter.org/

After installing bacon (having the executeable bacon script in your namespace /bin), just run


ape/psh
bacon (.bac file)


This will convert the BASIC source to C, which subsequently is compiled by your compiler